<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2610180>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Holotype of Parotocinclus yaka, female, 30.1 mm SL, MZUSP 123655. Brazil, Amazonas, Rio Tiquié basin, Igarapé Açaí near São Pedro Village." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2610180/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2610182>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Parotocinclus yaka, MZUSP 85786, head, lateral view, left side. Scale bar = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2610182/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2610184>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Color pattern of Parotocinclus showing markings of dorsum of head. A. Parotocinclus longirostris, MZUSP 85768; B. Parotocinclus polyochrus AMNH 74482, holotype); C. P. variola, MCP 48244; and D. P. yaka, MZUSP 81408. Scale bar = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2610184/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2610186>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Parotocinclus yaka, MZUSP 85786, dorsal-fin spinelet, dorsal view, anterior towards top. Scale bar = 500 µ." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2610186/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2610188>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Drainage map of the upper Amazon basin showing the localities of Parotocinclus yaka. Red dot symbol is typelocality and may represent more than one lot or locality." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2610188/files/figure.png" ;
